        "answer": "The separation rule says that shaded cells cannot touch each other horizontally or vertically.\n\nLet's say we try shading cell r1c2. Since r1c1 and r1c2 are next to each other, if we shade r1c2, then r1c1 must be unshaded to follow the separation rule.\n\nBut this creates a problem because we assumed r1c2 is shaded while r1c1 has to stay unshaded. This doesn't work because it would mean both cells are shaded in a way that breaks the separation rule.\n\nSo, our initial idea of shading r1c2 must be wrong. Therefore, r1c2 cannot be shaded and must remain unshaded.",
